    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-25T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-25T06:00:00-05:00" n="134"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/513: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-25T11:00:00+00:00"
                            >October 25, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 25—8 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>536. Department’s 313, October 24, 7 p.m. Following is text of first paragraphs
                    of invitation dated October 24:</p>
                <p>[Here follows text printed in <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_278">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, volume I, page
                        278</ref>.]</p>
                <p>I propose to answer this invitation by a formal note based on the first paragraph
                    of Department’s 313, October 24, 7 p.m. and failing <pb facs="0233" n="131"
                        xml:id="pg_131"/> immediate instructions to the contrary, in delivering this
                    written reply I assume it is the Department’s purpose that I convey orally the
                    substance of the Department’s 315, October 24, 9 p.m.</p>
                <p>The British précis of conversation referred to in my 522, October 17, 3 p.m. not
                    yet received.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
